<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-474-197  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 474 197.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Oct 1 1990 v4 n35 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Army taps two firms for RCAS. (Boeing Computer Services Co. andComputer Sciences Corp. selected to compete for Reserve ComponentAutomation System contract)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Army awards Boeing Computer Services Co and ComputerSciences Corp (CSC) $15 million-plus contracts to prepare for atwo-month long competitive demonstration of Reserve ComponentAutomation System (RCAS) solutions.andP;  The Army National Guard andReserve will automate their mobilization and administrativefunctions with RCAS, a $1 billion ADP military contract.andP;  Boeing'sand CSC's demonstrations will feature systems that integrateoffice automation, telecommunications and distributed data baseand processing capability.andP;  Tests will be held at each company'sfacility in the spring of 1991; Army Reserve units will operatethe computers to see how user-friendly the proposed systems are.andO;In late 1991, the Army's Information Systems Selection andAcquisition Agency will choose a single contractor to fieldcritical system elements.andP;  The acquisition program will span 12years.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Boeing Computer Services Co. (contracts)Computer Sciences Corp. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    CSC.andO;Topic:     United States. ArmyElectronic Data ProcessingOffice AutomationGovernment ContractsCompetitionUnited States. Army. Information Systems Selection and AcquisitionAgencyField Testing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>